longBusinessSummary: KAP AG, through its subsidiaries, primarily provides engineered products in Germany, rest of Europe, North/South America, Asia, and internationally. It operates through Engineered Products, Flexible Films, Surface Technologies, and Precision Components segments. The Engineered Products segment develops, manufactures, and sells technical textiles that are used in reinforcement for flexible feed pipes for the oil and gas industry, closures for insulin packaging for the pharmaceutical industry, reinforcement in premium tyres for the automotive industry, and reinforcement of conveyor belts and air springs in the field of road and rail transport. The Flexible Films segment develops, produces, and sells flexible films consisting of flexible packaging material for the consumer goods industry, energy-efficient underlays and roof sarking membranes, faÃ§ade membranes and screed membranes for roofing and construction industry, protective covering solutions for the agricultural sector, solutions for shading technology in the construction of greenhouses, fabric-reinforced swimming pool linings and films, protective clothing in medical applications, and high-end projection screens. The Surface Technologies segment develops and sells surface coating solutions for the furniture, food, mechanical engineering, electrical, and automotive sectors. The Precision Components segment develops, produces, and sells complex plastic and plastic-metal compound parts, such as plastic gears with extrusion-coated metal shafts and related metal products that are primarily used in special electronic or electro-mechanical drives. The company was formerly known as KAP Beteiligungs-AG and changed its name to KAP AG in July 2018. KAP AG is headquartered in Fulda, Germany.
